        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-26T19:38:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "There is no queuing in these locks, so as long as any goroutine holds a read lock on checkoutsMutex, we can\u0027t lock it here, and new compile tasks may still be triggered and obtain new read locks during that time.  That means that, if the bots are busy, this may not happen for hours.  Is that acceptable?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 223,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 224,
        "endChar": 31
      },
      "revId": "14881eb1553140c65179d950ca237bc122708084",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7f320a50_d4a72f2c",
        "filename": "android_compile/go/android_compile/checkouts.go",
        "patchSetId": 18
      },
      "lineNbr": 224,
      "author": {
        "id": 5145
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-27T12:01:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "From the docs at https://golang.org/pkg/sync/#RWMutex\n\n\"If a goroutine holds a RWMutex for reading and another goroutine might call Lock, no goroutine should expect to be able to acquire a read lock until the initial read lock is released. In particular, this prohibits recursive read locking. This is to ensure that the lock eventually becomes available; a blocked Lock call excludes new readers from acquiring the lock.\"",
      "parentUuid": "7118cdce_cb973584",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 223,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 224,
        "endChar": 31
      },
      "revId": "14881eb1553140c65179d950ca237bc122708084",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
